result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: from the Surety, Dated 4/20/2016 as to Bond Forfeiture

Case Recalled @ 2:42 PM: Defendant Dakota Hamilton Swank in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per ADA:  Resolution reached which will call for a 12 mo PPDA as to Ct No 1- sucessful completion will call for dismissal.  Defendant confirms resolution.  Def again advised of right to counsel.  Court accepts voluntary waiver of counsel.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct 1:  NC   Court accepts plea and stays JOC.  Count No 2 DRI.  Court accepts terms and conditions of PPDA.  Matter stayed for 1 yr.  Def reminded that bond continues during pendency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:42 PM: Defendant Dakota Hamilton Swank in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def states he wishes to speak with the State on his own on resolution without counsel.  Court orders $500 Signature Bond w/conditions.  Court advises Def that previous cash bond posted has been forfeited.  NGP entered by Court.   P/S Scheduled - NOH Given.  Def to speak with ADA immediately following Court today. Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 23, 2016 at 03:45 pm.
Voluntary appearance/Initial appearance on April 12, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
From defendant requesting a new hearing date.

Cases Called @ 2:22 PM: Defendant Dakota Hamilton Swank not in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Default judgment entered as to both 16TR-655 and 16TR-656. 16TR-655 RCS Issue:  Imposes $811.50, 6 mos DL Rev, no IID requirement, OWI assessment prior to relicensing occurs.  16TR-656 - bond imposed as per citation.  Court orders $200 bond forfeited with Arrest Warrant with Extradition within the State of Wisconsin.
